--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1. DEFINITION OF NON-COMMERCIAL USE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following uses are considered Non-Commercial and are permitted at no charge:

  (a) PERSONAL USE
      Use by a natural person for private, personal purposes, where no
      commercial activity is involved and no revenue is generated through
      or with the Software.

  (b) ACADEMIC AND RESEARCH USE
      Use by students, researchers, faculty, or staff at an accredited
      educational institution or non-commercial research organisation, for the
      purposes of education, academic research, or scholarly publication.
      This includes use in coursework, dissertations, published papers, and
      non-commercial research projects.

  (c) JOURNALISM AND PRESS
      Use by individual journalists, freelance reporters, and press
      organisations for the purpose of newsgathering, source protection,
      and the publication of journalism in the public interest, provided
      that the primary purpose of the organisation is the publication of
      news or editorial content and not the sale of software or services
      derived from the Software.

  (d) SECURITY RESEARCH
      Use for the purpose of identifying, analysing, and responsibly
      disclosing security vulnerabilities in the Software itself, provided
      that any findings are disclosed to the copyright holder before or
      concurrent with any public disclosure.

  Any use that does not fall within (a), (b), (c), or (d) above is
  Commercial Use and requires a Commercial Licence as set out in Part II.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  2. CONDITIONS FOR NON-COMMERCIAL USE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

All Non-Commercial use is subject to the following conditions:

  (a) ATTRIBUTION
      The above copyright notice and this licence must be included in all
      copies or substantial portions of the Software, whether in source
      or binary form.

  (b) PRESERVATION OF NOTICES
      You may not remove, obscure, or alter any copyright notice, licence
      notice, or attribution notice present in the Software.

  (c) NO MISREPRESENTATION
      You may not represent modified versions of the Software as the
      original, unmodified Software. If you distribute a modified version,
      you must clearly indicate that changes have been made.

  (d) SHARE-ALIKE FOR DISTRIBUTIONS
      If you distribute the Software or any derivative work under this
      Non-Commercial Licence, you must do so under the same licence terms
      as set out in this Part I. You may not apply additional restrictions
      that would prevent recipients from exercising the rights granted here.

  (e) NO SUBLICENSING
      You may not sublicence the Software to any third party. Third parties
      who wish to use the Software must obtain their own licence directly
      under these terms or under a Commercial Licence.

  (f) INTEGRITY OF SECURITY FEATURES
      You may not modify, disable, remove, or circumvent any encryption,
      authentication, or security mechanism present in the Software and
      then distribute that modified version to third parties.


================================================================================
  PART II — COMMERCIAL LICENCE
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  3. DEFINITION OF COMMERCIAL USE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Commercial Use means any use of the Software that does not qualify as
Non-Commercial Use under Part I, including but not limited to:

  (a) Use by a for-profit company, partnership, sole trader, or other
      commercial entity, regardless of company size or annual revenue.

  (b) Internal business communication, operations, or tooling at any
      commercial organisation.

  (c) Integration of the Software, in whole or in part, into a product
      or service that is sold, licensed, or offered for a fee.

  (d) Use by a commercial entity to provide managed services, hosting,
      or any service offering to third parties that relies on or includes
      the Software.

  (e) Use by a contractor, consultant, or freelancer on behalf of a
      commercial client.

  For the avoidance of doubt: an organisation is commercial if it operates
  with the primary purpose of generating profit, regardless of whether it
  is currently profitable.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  4. REQUIREMENT FOR COMMERCIAL LICENCE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Any Commercial Use of the Software requires a separate, written Commercial
Licence Agreement obtained directly from the copyright holder.

  (a) You must obtain a Commercial Licence BEFORE beginning any Commercial Use.

  (b) Use of the Software for Commercial purposes without a valid Commercial
      Licence is a material breach of this licence and an infringement of
      the copyright holder's rights.

  (c) To obtain a Commercial Licence, contact the copyright holder at the
      address or email set out at the end of this document.

  (d) Commercial Licences are granted on a per-organisation basis and are
      non-transferable without written consent from the copyright holder.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  5. COMMERCIAL LICENCE — GENERAL TERMS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Commercial Licences are issued on the following general terms unless otherwise
agreed in writing:

  (a) SCOPE
      A Commercial Licence grants the licensee the right to use the Software
      within their organisation for internal business communication and
      operations, in accordance with the specific terms agreed in the
      Commercial Licence Agreement.

  (b) MODIFICATIONS
      Commercial licensees may modify the Software for internal use. Any
      modifications that are distributed externally require written consent
      from the copyright holder.

  (c) NO RESALE WITHOUT AGREEMENT
      A Commercial Licence does not grant the right to resell, sublicence,
      or redistribute the Software or derivative works to third parties
      without a separate written reseller or OEM agreement.

  (d) AUDIT RIGHT
      The copyright holder reserves the right, on reasonable written notice,
      to audit the licensee's use of the Software to verify compliance with
      the Commercial Licence terms.

  (e) TERMINATION
      A Commercial Licence may be terminated by the copyright holder with
      written notice if the licensee materially breaches the licence terms
      and fails to remedy the breach within thirty (30) days of written
      notice.


